# Supplied and sensitive data

Use this module for personal, confidential, supplied, third-party, or persisted model data.

## Before processing

Record provenance, purpose, owner, classification, retention, deletion requirements, and allowed destinations.
Authorization to process data is not authorization to publish it or send it to every model,
assistant, tracing service, or evaluation provider.

## Minimize and contain

- Inspect only what is necessary to establish the schema and risk.
- Remove unnecessary fields before development or inference.
- Prefer independently synthetic fixtures for public tests and demonstrations.
- Treat chunks, prompts, responses, caches, embeddings, indexes, and evaluation sets as derived artifacts
  that can inherit source sensitivity.
- Keep originals immutable and separate from working and derived data when the project needs those stages.

Pseudonymization reduces direct identification risk. It does not prove anonymization or regulatory
compliance.

## Incidents and closure

Stop affected processing after an unintended disclosure, preserve facts, notify the accountable owner, and
follow the project's incident procedure. At closure, verify deletion or authorized retention of originals,
working copies, derived artifacts, logs, and external copies.
